  "Notes": [
    {
      "Text": "Security update for grub2",
      "Title": "Topic",
      "Type": "Summary"
    },
    {
      "Text": "\nThis update for grub2 rebuilds the existing package with the new 4k RSA secure boot key for IBM Power and Z.\n\nNote: the signing key of x86 / x86_64 and aarch64 architectures are unchanged.\n\nAlso the following issue were fixed:\n\n- CVE-2025-4382: TPM auto-decryption data exposure (bsc#1242971)\n- Fix segmentation fault error in grub2-probe with target=hints_string (bsc#1235971) (bsc#1235958) (bsc#1239651)\n",
      "Title": "Details",
      "Type": "General"
    },
